      • adapt

        public IComponent<?> adapt(Object object)
        Returns with the terminology independent component representation of the specified object after adapting it. Returns with null if the object cannot be adapted to any terminology independent component.
        This method swallows all the exceptions occurred during the adaption process and returns with null.
        Parameters:
        object - the object to adapt. Cannot be null.
        Returns:
        the terminology independent component.

      • getTerminologyBrowserFactory

        public IClientTerminologyBrowserFactory<String,IComponent<String>,IClientTerminologyBrowser<IComponent<String>,String>> getTerminologyBrowserFactory(String terminologyComponentId)
        Returns with the terminology browser factory for the given terminology component ID argument.

        If there are no registered terminology browser factories associated with the given terminology component ID, this method returns with a factory which creates an empty terminology browser. That empty terminology browser instance always returns with true for IClientTerminologyBrowser.isTerminologyAvailable() invocation.
